# Synthesizability gate for the TACCEL design — generic synth, NO FPGA part.
#
# File reads are supplied by the Makefile (single source of truth = CONTROL_SV,
# the taccel_top design set with tb/ excluded) via:
#   yosys -p "read_verilog -sv -I... <CONTROL_SV>" rtl/synth/synth_check.ys
#
# Definition of done (FPGA-demo roadmap Phase 2): this elaborates taccel_top to
# a synthesizable netlist with ZERO behavioral constructs (no `real`, no DPI-C).
# It is EXPECTED to fail today on sfu_engine.sv + blocking_helper_engine.sv
# (real storage + import "DPI-C"). That red IS the precise work list and the
# regression detector for the synthesizable-RTL effort.

# Resolve the module hierarchy from the real top; loud early error on any
# missing/unresolved module.
hierarchy -check -top taccel_top

# Generic, technology-independent synthesis (no FPGA part). Fails non-zero on
# any construct it cannot map to synthesizable logic — which is exactly the
# behavioral (real/DPI) surface we are eliminating.
synth -top taccel_top

# Structural sanity: assert on combinational loops, multiple drivers, etc.
check -assert

# First area/cell estimate — the number freeze §4.4 explicitly demands
# ("no synthesis number exists; should be measured before RTL sign-off").
stat
